A total of 13 bodies out of 23 people who were kept in the morgue of the Morogoro Regional Referral hospital after dying in a bus accident on Friday have been identified by relatives. Acting Communications Officer at Morogoro Regional Referral Hospital (MRRH), Scholastica Solomon revealed this in the presence of Regional Commissioner Martine Shigela as she added that seven people admitted at the facility have been discharged. Regional boss Martine Shigela visited the place to see the progress of injured people and the actual number of people whose deaths resulted from Fridayâ€™s horrific accident. Ms Scholastica said the referral hospital received 36 casualties of which seven were treated and discharged and the other 26 including 10 men, 15 women and one child were admitted for further medical treatments. Three injured people, two men and a woman were referred to Muhimbili National Hospital (MNH), including the Assistant Driver of the bus involved in the collision with a lorry. He has been identified as Hemed Ally. For his part, Regional Commissioner Martin Shigela has argued that motorists adhere to the road safety laws while they are on the road to avoid unnecessary accidents.